# Offline-First PWA Architecture

## Constraints

- App must function without network after initial PWA install and asset cache.
- No assumption of REST backend, WebSockets, or cloud document sync.
- Service worker config lives in `@vite.config.ts` (VitePWA plugin).

## Storage Split

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|------------|---------|
| Metadata | Dexie / IndexedDB | docs, sources, agents, settings, chunks index |
| Vectors | OPFS | embedding float32 blobs |
| Secrets | Encrypted IndexedDB | BYOK API keys |

## Compute

- Local LLM via `@src/lib/useLLM.ts` — WebGPU primary, WASM CPU fallback.
- Do not block UI thread with model load or inference; show loading states.

## Network Usage

- Allowed: optional BYOK provider calls, library metadata fetch, CDN model artifacts (documented in CSP).
- Forbidden: silent upload of user documents or embeddings.

## PWA Changes

- Manifest/icons in `vite.config.ts` and `public/`.
- Test offline via DevTools Application → Service Workers after `npm run build && npm run preview`.

